1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:13,400
<i>Jade is so weird. Right, Kutsy?</i>

2
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:15,833
<i>She really reminds me of Olive,
Wiro.</i>

3
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:17,133
<i> I'm calling off the wedding.</i>

4
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,967
<i> Don't do this to me, Danilo!</i>

5
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:20,533
<i>Please help me convince
your father</i>

6
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:22,300
<i>that he's making a big mistake.</i>

7
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,100
<i> I can't help you.</i>

8
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:25,733
<i> You really are ungrateful!</i>

9
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:27,367
<i>It's not often that I ask you
for a favor,</i>

10
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,567
<i> and you still won't help me!</i>

11
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,767
<i>Will you abandon me just like
that?</i>

12
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:33,800
<i>If I've done something
good to you and Mookie,</i>

13
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:37,433
<i>the least that you can do is
prepare me for the pain.</i>

14
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:38,900
<i> We're not leaving for now.</i>

15
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:40,833
<i>But I'll transfer
to another room</i>

16
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:43,433
<i>so that you'll get used
to sleeping without me.</i>

17
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:45,233
<i> You're such a good man.</i>

18
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:48,433
<i>I'll use that to keep you
from leaving me.</i>

19
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,433
<i> Danilo's leaving.</i>

20
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,100
<i>I think he's going
to meet with Emma.</i>

21
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:53,433
<i>Don't let them see each other
and talk.</i>

22
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:55,800
<i>Jade, that will be the end
of you.</i>

23
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:36,400
Hello, Caloy.

24
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:39,367
Keep an eye on Ligaya.

25
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,800
Make sure she won't escape.

26
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,933
And make sure no one sees you.

27
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:44,600
Bye.

28
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:45,600
Love!

29
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,667
Love, my stomach hurts! Please!

30
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:51,467
Love, help me, please!
Bring me to the hospital!

31
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,433
Love!

32
00:01:52,567 --> 00:01:53,500
Love!

33
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:56,000
No!

34
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,833
What are you doing?

35
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:13,167
Why are you touching me?
Who are you? I don't know you!

36
00:02:16,033 --> 00:02:17,100
This is for you.

37
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,367
Why did you give me this?

38
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:47,633
I know you never experienced
receiving gifts

39
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,167
when you were a kid.

40
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,300
I'm sorry,

41
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:57,400
that's all I can afford.

42
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:03,367
This is the first time

43
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:05,500
someone has given me something
like this.

44
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:15,200
Olive.

45
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:44,833
Danilo.

46
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,167
My daughter.

47
00:04:12,633 --> 00:04:13,800
Is it your break time?

48
00:04:15,067 --> 00:04:16,500
Get back to work!

49
00:04:20,067 --> 00:04:22,467
Boss, are you sure you're okay?

50
00:04:25,367 --> 00:04:27,600
This is just a hangover.

51
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:28,433
Come on.

52
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,767
Boss, that's not an ordinary
hangover.

53
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,533
You drank too much early
this morning.

54
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:38,533
You reek of alcohol.

55
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,167
You should've changed
your clothes.

56
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:43,867
You're so affected by Emma.

57
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:45,867
Hey!

58
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,567
Do you have a mouth spray?

59
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,900
Let me have it.

60
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:50,233
Hey!

61
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:51,633
Watch your mouth. You scumbag.

62
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,933
Let me remind you
that I'm your boss.

63
00:04:55,067 --> 00:04:56,200
I'm just concerned about you,
boss.

64
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,500
How can you impress Emma?

65
00:04:58,633 --> 00:05:00,300
- Emma's coming, boss.
- Give me that.

66
00:05:03,733 --> 00:05:04,467
Emma.

67
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,667
Did you drink?

68
00:05:11,167 --> 00:05:14,367
You better go home.

69
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,600
Take a bath.

70
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:18,033
The staff are here.
It's embarrassing.

71
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:19,900
They can't see you like that.

72
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:24,833
Where are you going?

73
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:26,767
Danilo and I are going to meet.

74
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:27,833
No!

75
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,233
I won't let that happen!

76
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:39,567
<i> Hurry up, Jade!</i>

77
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,967
I'm trying!

78
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,800
Wait, why didn't you go with me?

79
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:47,200
I'm taking care of something
important.

80
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:50,233
Wait. What will you tell Danilo?

81
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:50,967
I don't know.

82
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,300
I'll probably crash my car

83
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:54,733
so he'll pity me and bring me
to the hospital!

84
00:05:54,867 --> 00:05:55,867
I don't know!

85
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,133
What?

86
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:58,700
That's so pathetic!

87
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,167
Why is it...

88
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:11,600
Why did it stop?

89
00:06:11,733 --> 00:06:13,133
What's happening?

90
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,633
I don't know!

91
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:16,533
The car suddenly stopped!

92
00:06:17,567 --> 00:06:20,433
Of all the days!

93
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:26,167
Wait, Danilo's getting away.
This can't be!

94
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,267
And who told you I'm asking
for your permission?

95
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,800
You have no right to stop me.

96
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:43,600
I have the right, Emma.

97
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:48,567
You are my responsibility
because you're staying with me!

98
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,000
Can't you see?

99
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,800
I'm just protecting you!

100
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:52,900
From Danilo?

101
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:56,900
Logan, this is it.
My plans are finally paying off!

102
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:57,867
It's happening.

103
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,933
I can finally talk to him.

104
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:02,467
I can finally tell him
what really happened.

105
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,933
You'll meet with that bastard

106
00:07:05,067 --> 00:07:08,167
because you want to get back
together with him!

107
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,733
Excuse me!

108
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:10,833
Mister!

109
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:12,600
Mister, I need a ride.

110
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:26,633
What's wrong with you?

111
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:29,033
You've seen me getting on.
But you beat me to it!

112
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:30,600
How ungentleman!

113
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:31,900
Scooch!

114
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,967
-There's no more space, Ma'am.
-The space is already too tight.

115
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:35,900
What do you mean by no space?

116
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:37,767
Just scooch over!
I can still fit.

117
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:42,400
- There's no more space, Miss!
- Just stay there!

118
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,067
Mr. Driver,

119
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,933
please chase that red pick-up
truck in front of you!

120
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,900
Hurry! Chase it!

121
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:55,733
Why don't you get a taxi?

122
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:58,733
Stop complaining as if you're
all that!

123
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:00,767
I can pay for your lives!

124
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:05,900
- Go ahead, show us!
- Go ahead, show us!

125
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:07,733
You're not convinced?

126
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:09,600
Hold me. Hold me!

127
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,033
You think I'm lying?

128
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:13,767
There you go!

129
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,533
Come on and get it!

130
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:22,767
You're all greedy for money!

131
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:24,833
There you go!
Mister, chase that car!

132
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:28,733
- Go chase that car!
- Chase it! Faster!

133
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:31,133
Don't let him escape you!

134
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:32,533
Hold me!

135
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:33,867
I gave you money, didn't I?

136
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,200
Hold me!

137
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,200
You'll deal with me if I fall!

138
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:38,133
You...

139
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:41,767
Emma, you're a liar.

140
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:47,167
You told me you hate Danilo.

141
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,833
And you only wanted to take
Mookie back from him!

142
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:52,233
I even helped you with your
plans!

143
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,633
But look. After spending
a night with him,

144
00:08:56,800 --> 00:09:00,200
you're being a fool for him
again!

145
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:07,933
I helped you escape from Jade's
evilness and get even with her!

146
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:10,033
You took everything for granted!

147
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,700
Why are you keeping count
of the times you helped me?

148
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,633
Yes, I asked you for help.

149
00:09:15,767 --> 00:09:18,733
Because I thought you were
sincere about helping!

150
00:09:18,867 --> 00:09:20,567
Yes, I was willing.

151
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,633
Because I wanted you
to get even.

152
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:25,767
I wanted you to be happy
because I love you!

153
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,600
We talked about that already!

154
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:30,033
Logan, I'm sorry.

155
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:32,300
I can't reciprocate your love.

156
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,433
If only the heart could be
taught,

157
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:37,967
I would've loved you
a long time ago.

158
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:41,233
I wish my heart
was made of paper.

159
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:43,767
So I could erase my feelings.
So it could be easily replaced.

160
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,000
But it wasn't.

161
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:46,233
I'm sorry.

162
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:51,167
- No. No! You're not leaving!
- Ouch! What are you doing?

163
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,333
Don't block my way!

164
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,367
Come on, Emma!

165
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,100
Ouch! Stop!

166
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:01,333
Have you already forgotten
what he did to you?

167
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:06,067
What did he do when Jade drove
you crazy?

168
00:10:07,767 --> 00:10:08,500
Nothing!

169
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:11,067
He let you suffer.

170
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,967
<i>Will you give everyone
the attitude?</i>

171
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,533
<i>Why do you seem like you're
taking her side?</i>

172
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:19,167
<i> You and Mookie are the same!</i>

173
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:22,067
<i> All you talk about is Jade!</i>

174
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,533
<i> Jade has helped us a lot!</i>

175
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,400
<i>And now you're seeing her
in a bad light.</i>

176
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,233
<i>We're doing this for you, okay?</i>

177
00:10:27,367 --> 00:10:30,000
<i> What are you doing?</i>

178
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:31,400
<i> I'm not crazy!</i>

179
00:10:31,533 --> 00:10:33,667
<i> Don't let them take me!</i>

180
00:10:35,267 --> 00:10:38,100
The more I should talk
to Danilo.

181
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:39,400
Yes, you're right.

182
00:10:39,533 --> 00:10:42,333
I forgot about everything when
we spent the night together.

183
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:44,300
I'm not the only one who needs
to explain.

184
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:45,500
Danilo, too.

185
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,733
Hello?

186
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:51,200
Hello, Leticia. I'm in a jeep.
I'm riding a jeep.

187
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,800
I'm still chasing Danilo.

188
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,033
Jade, be careful.

189
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:55,333
You know me.

190
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:58,733
I don't give up when there's
something I need to get done.

191
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:02,167
I will do whatever it takes
just to catch Danilo.

192
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,567
Bye. Let's talk later.

193
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:05,200
Mister!

194
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,533
Mister, chase him!

195
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:08,833
Go! Chase him!

196
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:11,933
Ouch!

197
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,300
What are you doing?

198
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,633
I'm getting off!

199
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:24,133
Stop! Stop!

200
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:40,467
Hey, hey, hey!

201
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,033
Where do you think you're going?

202
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:44,333
What are you doing?

203
00:11:47,733 --> 00:11:49,533
I need to use this.
Can I borrow it?

204
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,433
I'll bring it back real quick...

205
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:51,833
No!

206
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,100
That's mine!

207
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:55,967
- Get off!
- Wait, wait!

208
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,467
You're so slow! Get off!

209
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:00,467
Here you go. Here.
This is yours.

210
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,000
Is everything okay now?
Is it okay now?

211
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:05,167
I'm easy to talk to.

212
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,733
- Fine.
- It's just that you're slow.

213
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:07,533
Wait!

214
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,267
Here you can have this.

215
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:10,767
Take it.

216
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:12,633
Thanks.

217
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:20,500
Ouch!

218
00:12:20,633 --> 00:12:21,467
Stop!

219
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,567
Will you really be a fool
for that man?

220
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:25,867
Think about it, Emma.

221
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:31,533
What if Danilo worked with
Jade to drive you insane?

222
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:34,267
What are you talking about?
Danilo can't do that!

223
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,133
Think about it, Emma!

224
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:43,167
Didn't Danilo convince you
to move to Jade's house before?

225
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:52,533
<i>I want us to live together
in one house.</i>

226
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,600
<i>There's enough space
for all of us there!</i>

227
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:56,433
<i> It's fun, right?</i>

228
00:12:56,567 --> 00:13:00,400
<i> Your sister only cares for us.</i>

229
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:02,133
And when you moved in,

230
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:03,433
what did you notice about them?

231
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,933
<i>Why did you talk to your sister
like that?</i>

232
00:13:07,067 --> 00:13:10,233
<i> She was just being kind to me.</i>

233
00:13:10,367 --> 00:13:15,533
And when you got better and came
back, what did you see?

234
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:18,767
<i> Will you marry me, Dan?</i>

235
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,667
<i> Will you marry me?</i>

236
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,667
<i> Yes, Jade.</i>

237
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:23,033
<i> Yes?</i>

238
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:24,600
<i> I'll marry you.</i>

239
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:26,833
<i> Oh, Dan!</i>

240
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:32,500
Don't you think she had already
seduced your ex

241
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:35,767
before you even moved
into her house?

242
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:38,867
Danilo and I will deal
with each other.

243
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,667
Emma, please.

244
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,233
Don't meet with Danilo.

245
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,700
Turn your attention to me.

246
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,900
I will love you.
I won't cheat on you.

247
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,067
Can you just be mine?

248
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:57,433
Logan.

249
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:58,467
Logan, please.

250
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,467
Danilo and I need to talk.

251
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:17,767
You still left.

252
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,533
You can't say no to me!

253
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:27,467
Why did you leave?

254
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:32,167
Why are you watching?

255
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:34,033
What's your problem?

256
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:35,700
Get back to work!

257
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,867
No one can say no to Logan.

258
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,100
No one can reject me!

259
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:04,633
Where are you, Danilo?

260
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:06,467
Where did you go?

261
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:10,333
I will find you, no matter what.

262
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,933
<i>What you'll do isn't easy,
Ligaya.</i>

263
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:35,433
<i> It could put you in danger.</i>

264
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:39,367
<i> But no matter what happens,</i>

265
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:42,400
<i> you must not give up.</i>

266
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:46,967
<i>Olive is not the only one you
need to save.</i>

267
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:50,833
<i> Mookie, too.</i>

268
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:57,033
<i>I must put an end to Olive's
wickedness.</i>

269
00:15:57,167 --> 00:16:01,767
<i>I need to take her to a doctor.</i>

270
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,033
<i> Because if not,</i>

271
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:03,967
<i>my granddaughter's life might
also be put in danger</i>

272
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:05,400
<i> because of her.</i>

273
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,200
<i> Let's go.</i>

274
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,867
<i> Why?</i>

275
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:23,233
<i>You told me about Jade, Olive,
and Emma.</i>

276
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:27,167
<i>You haven't told me enough about
Mookie.</i>

277
00:16:31,067 --> 00:16:32,033
<i> Mookie?</i>

278
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:36,233
<i> That kid is so kind.</i>

279
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,700
<i> She's so sweet.</i>

280
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:43,500
<i>Maybe it's because she was
longing for love</i>

281
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:45,700
<i> when she wasn't with us yet.</i>

282
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:47,533
<i>That's why when we were
finally together,</i>

283
00:16:47,667 --> 00:16:50,500
<i>we made her feel she was very
much loved.</i>

284
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:52,167
<i> Especially Emma.</i>

285
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:57,133
<i>Mookie poured all her love
on us.</i>

286
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:59,067
<i> You'll get fond of her.</i>

287
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:03,067
<i> Our granddaughter is smart.</i>

288
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,800
<i> Talented.</i>

289
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:09,033
<i>She's good at singing
and drawing.</i>

290
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:10,567
<i> She even drew me.</i>

291
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:15,333
<i> I hope to meet her.</i>

292
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:20,100
<i> Don't worry.</i>

293
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:23,967
<i> Let's pray for it to happen.</i>

294
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:25,567
<i> That day will come.</i>

295
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,700
<i> I just need...</i>

296
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:31,800
<i>to succeed with my plan with
Olive.</i>

297
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,867
<i>You just have to believe,
Ligaya.</i>

298
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:43,200
<i>I'll help you as long
as you need it.</i>

299
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,967
<i> Always remember,</i>

300
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:52,000
<i>don't give up no matter how
difficult things become.</i>

301
00:17:54,667 --> 00:17:55,667
<i> Yes, Ador.</i>

302
00:17:57,133 --> 00:18:07,100
<i> I will never give up.</i>

303
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:21,267
<i> Wait for me, Ligaya.</i>

304
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:25,733
<i>I won't stop until I let you out
of there.</i>

305
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:28,900
<i>I'll help you get our eldest
treated.</i>

306
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:30,200
<i> Maybe that can make up</i>

307
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:33,267
<i>for at least a little of what
I've done wrong to you.</i>

308
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,800
<i> To all of you.</i>

309
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,500
<i> I can climb up there.</i>

310
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,967
Thank you, Mister.

311
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,467
Thank you, Chona.

312
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:59,500
Are Uncle Wiro and Aunt Kutsy
there already?

313
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:02,900
My granddaughter?

314
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:07,500
Are Uncle Wiro and Aunt Kutsy
there already?

315
00:19:07,633 --> 00:19:09,933
Shouldn't you know about that
because they are your friends?

316
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:14,133
Excuse me, Ma'am.
I still have to clean the floor.

317
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:15,933
Okay.

318
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:32,400
Mookie!

319
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,167
Zayn, what are you doing here
again?

320
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,700
You're so stubborn.

321
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:41,667
Are you worried again
that my mom will see us here?

322
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,267
Zayn, I know what you're doing.

323
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,633
What do you mean?

324
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:48,500
You want to pursue me again.

325
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:51,400
Sorry, Zayn, but no.

326
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:53,633
We've cleared things already,
okay?

327
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:55,967
And we can't be more than
friends.

328
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,833
That's all we are. No big deal.

329
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:02,033
I could go in as your friend
back then.

330
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:07,567
Unless you don't want us
to be just friends.

331
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:10,800
Zayn, please,
let's not complicate things.

332
00:20:10,933 --> 00:20:13,967
Right. Don't complicate it.

333
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:15,133
If you're letting him in,
anyway,

334
00:20:15,267 --> 00:20:16,400
you might as well do it now.

335
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:18,333
Come on, youngsters.

336
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:21,867
Can you save the romance
for later?

337
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,200
Yes.

338
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:27,133
Because we don't want to be late
for Jade's late lunch gathering.

339
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:29,567
Uncle Wiro, Aunt Kutsy, why...

340
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:33,100
Mookie, we couldn't get a taxi.

341
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:37,000
So we called Zayn
to drive for us.

342
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:40,267
Can he join us?

343
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,767
Look, he got tired.

344
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:42,667
So pitiful.

345
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:43,667
Yeah.

346
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,633
Do I have a choice?

347
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:51,200
Looks like my friend
has conspired with you.

348
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:57,467
- Yes, friend. That's right.
- Come inside. Come on, friend.

349
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,533
Let's get inside, friend.

350
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:01,933
Yes, friend.

351
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:04,933
Turn off the engine first.
We'll go ahead.

352
00:21:05,067 --> 00:21:06,000
Let's go.

353
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,700
We're ready for the late lunch.

354
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:13,967
- Where are you going?
- To your heart.

355
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:22,200
<i>What if Danilo worked with Jade
to drive you insane?</i>

356
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:26,200
<i>Don't you think she had
already seduced your ex</i>

357
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:28,400
<i>before you even moved into her
house?</i>

358
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:33,233
Hello, Danilo? Where are you?

359
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,000
<i> I'm almost there, Emma.</i>

360
00:21:37,967 --> 00:21:40,033
Are you here now,
or are you just about to enter?

361
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,333
Hello?

362
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:44,433
Dan.

363
00:21:44,567 --> 00:21:46,367
Hello? Come on!

364
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,533
Show yourself if you're here.

365
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:52,167
I'm almost right next to you.

366
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:18,067
Why did you slap me?

367
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:23,933
Were you part of Jade's plan
to mess with my head?

368
00:22:24,967 --> 00:22:26,433
Emma, I don't know anything
about that.

369
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,433
When I was slowly losing
my sanity,

370
00:22:29,567 --> 00:22:31,467
you did nothing but take Jade's
side.

371
00:22:33,033 --> 00:22:34,933
You actually agreed to send me
to Havenwood.

372
00:22:35,067 --> 00:22:37,133
Emma, listen to me.

373
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:39,967
I didn't know what Jade
was doing.

374
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:43,133
But why did you say yes
to marrying her

375
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:45,067
when I've only been missing
for less than six months?

376
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:55,600
Ligaya?

377
00:22:57,033 --> 00:22:58,100
Ligaya, is that you?

378
00:22:58,233 --> 00:23:03,767
Once Ligaya hears about
your reunion with Emma,

379
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:07,233
your grandmother will show up.

380
00:23:08,267 --> 00:23:09,333
- Hopefully.
- Hopefully.

381
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:11,800
Hey!

382
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:13,200
Who are you?

383
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:17,433
Your car is here.

384
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:20,567
So that means you're here.

385
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:23,300
I'm gonna find you, Danilo.

386
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:26,833
You cheated on Emma and left her
for her crazy sister,

387
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:28,900
and now you want to get back
together with her

388
00:23:29,033 --> 00:23:30,100
like you didn't do anything
wrong?

389
00:23:30,233 --> 00:23:31,767
You don't know the whole story.

390
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:34,567
So stay out of it.

391
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,433
No.

392
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:39,033
I won't stop meddling
in your business

393
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,800
if you don't leave Emma alone!

394
00:23:43,133 --> 00:23:47,867
Ligaya!
